      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I don't think we need an approach like #14489 that replaces all sleep calls with interruptiblesleep, only the relevant ones in the mentioned cases.\r\n\r\nIt looks like there is already a helper class for interruptible sleeps:\r\n```c++\r\n/*\r\n    A helper class for interruptible sleeps. Calling operator() will interrupt\r\n    any current sleep, and after that point operator bool() will return true\r\n    until reset.\r\n*/\r\nclass CThreadInterrupt\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo I think it's a matter of using these in the right places?\r\n",
